result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Rodolfo Aguilera Jr was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person with Attorney Osborne.  No victim interest in this case.  Defendant plead guilty to Count 1.  Count 2 dismissed by operation of law.   Court advised the defendant of the possible penalties of the charge he is pleading to.  He understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood. Priors recited in court by the district attorney.  Priors verified by defense.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Count 1.  Joint recommendation for $3,264.00 125 days jail.  30 mo. DL rev & IID.  Alcohol assmt and driver's safety plan.  Court ordered:  $3,264.00,  125 days jail, to commence immediately.  EMP allowed according to jail rules.    30 mo. DL rev & IID.  Alcohol assmt and driver's safety plan.  Pay fine @ 100/mo starting 5/1/16.  Failure to pay any part of the fine and court costs will result in 30 days jail.    Court advised defendant of the DNA submission requirement.
